panning¶

Classes

Splay

A stereo signal spreader.
class supriya.ugens.panning.Splay[source]¶

A stereo signal spreader.

>>> source = supriya.ugens.SinOsc.ar(frequency=[333, 444, 555, 666, 777])
>>> splay = supriya.ugens.Splay.ar(source=source)

>>> print(splay)

A stereo signal balancer.

A 2D ambisonic b-format panner.

A 2D Ambisonic B-format decoder.

A two channel equal power panner.

A four-channel equal-power panner.

A multi-channel equal-power panner.

class supriya.ugens.panning.Balance2(calculation_rate=None, left=None, right=None, position=0.0, level=1.0)[source]¶

A stereo signal balancer.

>>> left = supriya.ugens.WhiteNoise.ar()
>>> right = supriya.ugens.SinOsc.ar()
>>> balance_2 = supriya.ugens.Balance2.ar(
...     left=left, level=1, position=0, right=right,
... )
>>> balance_2
UGenArray({2})

Attributes Summary

ar

Constructs a audio-rate Balance2 unit generator graph.

kr

Constructs a control-rate Balance2 unit generator graph.

left

Gets left of Balance2.

level

Gets level of Balance2.

position

Gets position of Balance2.

right

Gets right of Balance2.

Special methods

(UGenMethodMixin).__abs__()¶

Gets absolute value of ugen graph.

Example 1:

>>> ugen_graph = supriya.ugens.WhiteNoise.ar()
>>> result = abs(ugen_graph)
>>> result
UnaryOpUGen.ar()

>>> supriya.graph(result)  

>>> print(result)
synthdef:
    name: f21696d155a2686700992f0e9a04a79c
    ugens:
    -   WhiteNoise.ar: null
    -   UnaryOpUGen(ABSOLUTE_VALUE).ar:
            source: WhiteNoise.ar[0]

Example 2:

>>> ugen_graph = supriya.ugens.SinOsc.ar(frequency=(440, 442, 443),)
>>> result = abs(ugen_graph)
>>> result
UGenArray({3})

>>> supriya.graph(result)  

>>> print(result)
synthdef:
    name: 1d45df2f3d33d1b0641d2c464498f6c4
    ugens:
    -   SinOsc.ar/0:
            frequency: 440.0
            phase: 0.0
    -   UnaryOpUGen(ABSOLUTE_VALUE).ar/0:
            source: SinOsc.ar/0[0]
    -   SinOsc.ar/1:
            frequency: 442.0
            phase: 0.0
    -   UnaryOpUGen(ABSOLUTE_VALUE).ar/1:
            source: SinOsc.ar/1[0]
    -   SinOsc.ar/2:
            frequency: 443.0
            phase: 0.0
    -   UnaryOpUGen(ABSOLUTE_VALUE).ar/2:
            source: SinOsc.ar/2[0]

Returns ugen graph.

(UGenMethodMixin).__add__(expr)¶

Adds expr to ugen graph.

Example 1:

>>> ugen_graph = supriya.ugens.WhiteNoise.kr()
>>> expr = supriya.ugens.SinOsc.ar()
>>> result = ugen_graph + expr
>>> result

>>> print(result)

            left: WhiteNoise.kr[0]
            right: SinOsc.ar[0]

Example 2:

>>> result = ugen_graph + expr

>>> supriya.graph(result)  

>>> print(result)

    name: f4a3c1ed35cc5f6fe66b70a3bc520b10
    ugens:
    -   WhiteNoise.kr: null
    -   SinOsc.ar/0:
            frequency: 440.0

    -   BinaryOpUGen(ADDITION).ar/0:

            right: SinOsc.ar/0[0]

            frequency: 442.0

(UGenMethodMixin).__mul__(expr)¶

Multiplies ugen graph by expr.

Example 1:

>>> ugen_graph = supriya.ugens.WhiteNoise.kr()
>>> expr = supriya.ugens.SinOsc.ar()
>>> result = ugen_graph * expr
>>> result

>>> supriya.graph(result)  

>>> print(result)
synthdef:
    name: ea2b5e5cec4e2d5a1bef0a8dda522bd3
    ugens:
    -   WhiteNoise.kr: null
    -   SinOsc.ar:
            frequency: 440.0
            phase: 0.0
    -   BinaryOpUGen(MULTIPLICATION).ar:
            left: WhiteNoise.kr[0]
            right: SinOsc.ar[0]

Class & static methods

classmethod ar(left=None, right=None, position=0.0, level=1.0)¶

Constructs a audio-rate Balance2 unit generator graph.

Returns unit generator graph.

classmethod kr(left=None, right=None, position=0.0, level=1.0)¶

Constructs a control-rate Balance2 unit generator graph.

Returns unit generator graph.

Read-only properties

(UGen).calculation_rate¶

Gets calculation-rate of ugen.

>>> ugen = supriya.ugens.SinOsc.ar(
...     frequency=supriya.ugens.WhiteNoise.kr(), phase=0.5,
... )
>>> ugen.calculation_rate
CalculationRate.AUDIO

Returns calculation-rate.

(MultiOutUGen).channel_count¶

Gets channel count of multi-output ugen.

Returns integer.

(UGen).inputs¶

...     frequency=supriya.ugens.WhiteNoise.kr(), phase=0.5,
... )
>>> for input_ in ugen.inputs:
...     input_
...

0.5

Returns tuple.

(UGen).signal_range¶

Gets signal range of ugen.

>>> ugen = supriya.ugens.SinOsc.ar()
>>> ugen.signal_range
SignalRange.BIPOLAR

A bipolar signal range indicates that the ugen generates signals above and below zero.

A unipolar signal range indicates that the ugen only generates signals of 0 or greater.

Returns signal range.

(UGen).special_index¶

Gets special index of ugen.

>>> ugen = supriya.ugens.SinOsc.ar(
...     frequency=supriya.ugens.WhiteNoise.kr(), phase=0.5,
... )
>>> ugen.special_index
0

The special index of most ugens will be 0. SuperColliders’s synth definition file format uses the special index to store the operator id for binary and unary operator ugens, and the parameter index of controls.

Returns integer.

class supriya.ugens.panning.BiPanB2(calculation_rate=None, in_a=None, in_b=None, azimuth=None, gain=1.0)[source]¶

(UGen).signal_range¶

Gets signal range of ugen.

>>> ugen = supriya.ugens.SinOsc.ar()
>>> ugen.signal_range
SignalRange.BIPOLAR

A bipolar signal range indicates that the ugen generates signals above and below zero.

A unipolar signal range indicates that the ugen only generates signals of 0 or greater.

Returns signal range.

(UGen).special_index¶

Gets special index of ugen.

>>> ugen = supriya.ugens.SinOsc.ar(
...     frequency=supriya.ugens.WhiteNoise.kr(), phase=0.5,
... )
>>> ugen.special_index
0

The special index of most ugens will be 0. SuperColliders’s synth definition file format uses the special index to store the operator id for binary and unary operator ugens, and the parameter index of controls.

Returns integer.

(UGen).signal_range¶

Gets signal range of ugen.

>>> ugen = supriya.ugens.SinOsc.ar()
>>> ugen.signal_range
SignalRange.BIPOLAR

A bipolar signal range indicates that the ugen generates signals above and below zero.

A unipolar signal range indicates that the ugen only generates signals of 0 or greater.

Returns signal range.

(UGen).special_index¶

Gets special index of ugen.

>>> ugen = supriya.ugens.SinOsc.ar(
...     frequency=supriya.ugens.WhiteNoise.kr(), phase=0.5,
... )
>>> ugen.special_index
0

The special index of most ugens will be 0. SuperColliders’s synth definition file format uses the special index to store the operator id for binary and unary operator ugens, and the parameter index of controls.

Returns integer.

w¶

Gets w of DecodeB2.

Returns input.

x¶

Gets x of DecodeB2.

Returns input.

y¶

Gets y of DecodeB2.

Returns input.

(UGen).signal_range¶

Gets signal range of ugen.

>>> ugen = supriya.ugens.SinOsc.ar()
>>> ugen.signal_range
SignalRange.BIPOLAR

A bipolar signal range indicates that the ugen generates signals above and below zero.

A unipolar signal range indicates that the ugen only generates signals of 0 or greater.

Returns signal range.

source¶

Gets source of Pan2.

Returns input.

(UGen).special_index¶

Gets special index of ugen.

>>> ugen = supriya.ugens.SinOsc.ar(
...     frequency=supriya.ugens.WhiteNoise.kr(), phase=0.5,
... )
>>> ugen.special_index
0

The special index of most ugens will be 0. SuperColliders’s synth definition file format uses the special index to store the operator id for binary and unary operator ugens, and the parameter index of controls.

Returns integer.

    -   SinOsc.ar:
            frequency: 440.0
            phase: 0.0

(UGenMethodMixin).__sub__(expr)¶

Subtracts expr from ugen graph.

Example 1:

>>> ugen_graph = supriya.ugens.WhiteNoise.kr()
>>> expr = supriya.ugens.SinOsc.ar()
>>> result = ugen_graph - expr
>>> result
BinaryOpUGen.ar()

>>> supriya.graph(result)  

>>> print(result)
synthdef:
    name: cd62fff8ff3ad7758d0f7ad82f39c7ce
    ugens:
    -   WhiteNoise.kr: null
    -   SinOsc.ar:
            frequency: 440.0
            phase: 0.0
    -   BinaryOpUGen(SUBTRACTION).ar:
            left: WhiteNoise.kr[0]
            right: SinOsc.ar[0]

Example 2:

>>> expr = supriya.ugens.SinOsc.ar(frequency=[440, 442, 443],)
>>> result = ugen_graph - expr
>>> result

>>> supriya.graph(result)  

>>> print(result)
synthdef:
    name: 9a8355f84507908cadf3cc63187ddab4
    ugens:
    -   WhiteNoise.kr: null
    -   SinOsc.ar/0:
            frequency: 440.0
            phase: 0.0
    -   BinaryOpUGen(SUBTRACTION).ar/0:
            left: WhiteNoise.kr[0]
            right: SinOsc.ar/0[0]
    -   SinOsc.ar/1:
            frequency: 442.0
            phase: 0.0
    -   BinaryOpUGen(SUBTRACTION).ar/1:
            left: WhiteNoise.kr[0]
            right: SinOsc.ar/1[0]
    -   SinOsc.ar/2:
            frequency: 443.0
            phase: 0.0
    -   BinaryOpUGen(SUBTRACTION).ar/2:
            left: WhiteNoise.kr[0]
            right: SinOsc.ar/2[0]

Example 3:

>>> ugen_graph = supriya.ugens.Dust.ar(density=11.5,)
>>> expr = 4
>>> result = ugen_graph - expr
>>> result
BinaryOpUGen.ar()

>>> result = ugen_graph.semitones_to_ratio()

>>> supriya.graph(result)  

>>> print(result)
synthdef:
    name: f77ac2c24b06f8e620817f14285c2877
    ugens:
    -   WhiteNoise.ar: null
    -   UnaryOpUGen(SEMITONES_TO_RATIO).ar:
            source: WhiteNoise.ar[0]

Returns ugen graph.

(UGen).signal_range¶

Gets signal range of ugen.

>>> ugen = supriya.ugens.SinOsc.ar()
>>> ugen.signal_range
SignalRange.BIPOLAR

A bipolar signal range indicates that the ugen generates signals above and below zero.

A unipolar signal range indicates that the ugen only generates signals of 0 or greater.

Returns signal range.

source¶

Gets source of Pan4.

Returns input.

(UGen).special_index¶

Gets special index of ugen.

>>> ugen = supriya.ugens.SinOsc.ar(
...     frequency=supriya.ugens.WhiteNoise.kr(), phase=0.5,
... )
>>> ugen.special_index
0

The special index of most ugens will be 0. SuperColliders’s synth definition file format uses the special index to store the operator id for binary and unary operator ugens, and the parameter index of controls.

Returns integer.

x_position¶

Gets x_position of Pan4.

Returns input.

y_position¶

Gets y_position of Pan4.

Returns input.

(UGenMethodMixin).__mod__(expr)¶

Example 1:

>>> ugen_graph = supriya.ugens.WhiteNoise.kr()
>>> expr = supriya.ugens.SinOsc.ar()
>>> result = ugen_graph % expr
>>> result

>>> supriya.graph(result)

            phase: 0.0

            left: WhiteNoise.kr[0]
            right: SinOsc.ar[0]

(UGen).signal_range¶

Gets signal range of ugen.

>>> ugen = supriya.ugens.SinOsc.ar()
>>> ugen.signal_range
SignalRange.BIPOLAR

A bipolar signal range indicates that the ugen generates signals above and below zero.

A unipolar signal range indicates that the ugen only generates signals of 0 or greater.

Returns signal range.

source¶

Gets source of PanAz.

Returns input.

(UGen).special_index¶

Gets special index of ugen.

>>> ugen = supriya.ugens.SinOsc.ar(
...     frequency=supriya.ugens.WhiteNoise.kr(), phase=0.5,
... )
>>> ugen.special_index
0

The special index of most ugens will be 0. SuperColliders’s synth definition file format uses the special index to store the operator id for binary and unary operator ugens, and the parameter index of controls.

Returns integer.

width¶

Gets width of PanAz.

Returns input.

Class & static methods

classmethod ar(source=None, azimuth=0, elevation=0, gain=1)¶

Constructs a audio-rate PanB unit generator graph.

Returns unit generator graph.

classmethod kr(source=None, azimuth=0, elevation=0, gain=1)¶

Constructs a control-rate PanB unit generator graph.

Returns unit generator graph.

Read-only properties

Gets azimuth of PanB.

Returns input.

Returns tuple.

(UGen).signal_range¶

Gets signal range of ugen.

>>> ugen = supriya.ugens.SinOsc.ar()
>>> ugen.signal_range
SignalRange.BIPOLAR

A bipolar signal range indicates that the ugen generates signals above and below zero.

A unipolar signal range indicates that the ugen only generates signals of 0 or greater.

Returns signal range.

source¶

Gets source of PanB.

Returns input.

(UGen).special_index¶

Gets special index of ugen.

>>> ugen = supriya.ugens.SinOsc.ar(
...     frequency=supriya.ugens.WhiteNoise.kr(), phase=0.5,
... )
>>> ugen.special_index
0

The special index of most ugens will be 0. SuperColliders’s synth definition file format uses the special index to store the operator id for binary and unary operator ugens, and the parameter index of controls.

Returns integer.

class supriya.ugens.panning.PanB2(calculation_rate=None, source=None, azimuth=0, gain=1)[source]¶

(UGenMethodMixin).__abs__()¶

Gets absolute value of ugen graph.

>>> ugen_graph = supriya.ugens.WhiteNoise.ar()
>>> result = abs(ugen_graph)
>>> result
UnaryOpUGen.ar()

>>> supriya.graph(result)  

>>> print(result)
synthdef:
    name: f21696d155a2686700992f0e9a04a79c

Class & static methods

classmethod ar(source=None, azimuth=0, gain=1)¶

Constructs a audio-rate PanB2 unit generator graph.

Returns unit generator graph.

classmethod kr(source=None, azimuth=0, gain=1)¶

Constructs a control-rate PanB2 unit generator graph.

Returns unit generator graph.

Read-only properties

azimuth¶

Gets azimuth of PanB2.

Returns input.

Gets calculation-rate of ugen.

...     frequency=supriya.ugens.WhiteNoise.kr(), phase=0.5,
... )

CalculationRate.AUDIO

Returns calculation-rate.

(UGen).signal_range¶

Gets signal range of ugen.

>>> ugen = supriya.ugens.SinOsc.ar()
>>> ugen.signal_range
SignalRange.BIPOLAR

A bipolar signal range indicates that the ugen generates signals above and below zero.

A unipolar signal range indicates that the ugen only generates signals of 0 or greater.

Returns signal range.

source¶

Gets source of PanB2.

Returns input.

(UGen).special_index¶

Gets special index of ugen.

>>> ugen = supriya.ugens.SinOsc.ar(
...     frequency=supriya.ugens.WhiteNoise.kr(), phase=0.5,
... )
>>> ugen.special_index
0

The special index of most ugens will be 0. SuperColliders’s synth definition file format uses the special index to store the operator id for binary and unary operator ugens, and the parameter index of controls.

Returns integer.

class supriya.ugens.panning.Rotate2(calculation_rate=None, x=None, y=None, position=0)[source]¶

Equal-power sound-field rotator.

>>> x = supriya.ugens.PinkNoise.ar() * 0.4
>>> y = supriya.ugens.LFTri.ar(frequency=880)
>>> y *= supriya.ugens.LFPulse.kr(frequency=3, width=0.1)
>>> position = supriya.ugens.LFSaw.kr(frequency=0.1)
>>> rotate_2 = supriya.ugens.Rotate2.ar(x=x, y=y, position=position,)
>>> rotate_2
UGenArray({2})

Returns an array of the rotator’s left and right outputs.

Attributes Summary

ar

Constructs a audio-rate Rotate2 unit generator graph.

kr

Constructs a control-rate Rotate2 unit generator graph.

position

Gets position of Rotate2.

x

Gets x of Rotate2.

y

Gets y of Rotate2.

classmethod ar(x=None, y=None, position=0)¶

Constructs a audio-rate Rotate2 unit generator graph.

Returns unit generator graph.

classmethod kr(x=None, y=None, position=0)¶

Constructs a control-rate Rotate2 unit generator graph.

Returns unit generator graph.

(UGen).signal_range¶

Gets signal range of ugen.

>>> ugen = supriya.ugens.SinOsc.ar()
>>> ugen.signal_range
SignalRange.BIPOLAR

A bipolar signal range indicates that the ugen generates signals above and below zero.

A unipolar signal range indicates that the ugen only generates signals of 0 or greater.

Returns signal range.

(UGen).special_index¶

Gets special index of ugen.

>>> ugen = supriya.ugens.SinOsc.ar(
...     frequency=supriya.ugens.WhiteNoise.kr(), phase=0.5,
... )
>>> ugen.special_index
0

The special index of most ugens will be 0. SuperColliders’s synth definition file format uses the special index to store the operator id for binary and unary operator ugens, and the parameter index of controls.

Returns integer.

x¶

Gets x of Rotate2.

Returns input.

y¶

Gets y of Rotate2.

Returns input.

(UGenMethodMixin).__gt__(expr)¶

Tests if ugen graph if greater than expr.

Example 1:

>>> ugen_graph = supriya.ugens.WhiteNoise.kr()
>>> expr = supriya.ugens.SinOsc.ar()
>>> result = ugen_graph > expr

(UGenMethodMixin).scale(input_minimum, input_maximum, output_minimum, output_maximum, exponential=False)¶

Scales ugen graph from input_minimum and input_maximum to output_minimum and output_maximum.

>>> ugen_graph = supriya.ugens.WhiteNoise.ar()
>>> result = ugen_graph.scale(-1, 1, 0.5, 0.75)

>>> supriya.graph(result)  

>>> print(result)
synthdef:
    name: e2295e64ed7b9c949ec22ccdc82520e3
    ugens:
    -   WhiteNoise.ar: null
    -   MulAdd.ar:
            addend: 0.625
            multiplier: 0.125
            source: WhiteNoise.ar[0]


>>> ugen_graph = supriya.ugens.SinOsc.ar(frequency=[440, 442, 443],)
>>> result = ugen_graph.scale(-1, 1, 0.5, 0.75, exponential=True)

>>> supriya.graph(result)  

>>> print(result)

            frequency: 500.0

            frequency: 440.0
            phase: 0.0
    -   SinOsc.ar/1:

            input_one: SinOsc.ar/0[0]

Class & static methods

classmethod ar(in_a=None, in_b=0, pan=0, level=1)¶

Constructs a audio-rate XFade2 unit generator graph.

Returns unit generator graph.

classmethod kr(in_a=None, in_b=0, pan=0, level=1)¶

Constructs a control-rate XFade2 unit generator graph.

Returns unit generator graph.

Read-only properties

(UGen).calculation_rate¶

Gets calculation-rate of ugen.

>>> ugen = supriya.ugens.SinOsc.ar(
...     frequency=supriya.ugens.WhiteNoise.kr(), phase=0.5,
... )
>>> ugen.calculation_rate
CalculationRate.AUDIO

Returns calculation-rate.

(UGen).signal_range¶

Gets signal range of ugen.

>>> ugen = supriya.ugens.SinOsc.ar()
>>> ugen.signal_range
SignalRange.BIPOLAR

A bipolar signal range indicates that the ugen generates signals above and below zero.

A unipolar signal range indicates that the ugen only generates signals of 0 or greater.

Returns signal range.

(UGen).special_index¶

Gets special index of ugen.

>>> ugen = supriya.ugens.SinOsc.ar(
...     frequency=supriya.ugens.WhiteNoise.kr(), phase=0.5,
... )
>>> ugen.special_index
0

The special index of most ugens will be 0. SuperColliders’s synth definition file format uses the special index to store the operator id for binary and unary operator ugens, and the parameter index of controls.

Returns integer.
